1
00:01:28,960 --> 00:01:30,590
上
Now.

2
00:02:15,680 --> 00:02:20,640
出什么事了？不要！不要！
What's happening? Please! No! No!

3
00:02:25,820 --> 00:02:28,410
不要！求你了！别开枪！
No! Please! No!

4
00:02:37,930 --> 00:02:39,230
他不是墨索里尼！
That's not Mussolini.

5
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:43,170
不,不,他已经不在这里了！
No, no. Il Duce is not here anymore.

6
00:02:43,340 --> 00:02:46,210
他今早跟上校一起走了。他现在不在这里
He left this morning with colonel. He's not here now.

7
00:02:46,370 --> 00:02:48,500
我对天发誓！
I swear to God.

8
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:51,970
小姐,你最好穿上衣服
Look, signorina, you better put some clothes on.

9
00:02:52,150 --> 00:02:54,710
几分钟后游击队马上就来镇上了...
This village is gonna be full of partisans in a minute...

10
00:02:54,880 --> 00:02:57,820
...他们会来收集情报什么的
...and they'll be looking for information or something.

11
00:03:24,980 --> 00:03:27,680
敬富兰克林.罗斯福
Franklin Delano Roosevelt.

12
00:03:32,050 --> 00:03:34,780
温斯顿.丘吉尔
Winston Spenser Churchill.

13
00:04:14,700 --> 00:04:16,930
早上好,少校！将军正在等你
Good morning, major. The general's expecting you.

14
00:04:17,100 --> 00:04:18,430
谢谢！
Thank you.

15
00:04:21,300 --> 00:04:22,960
莱特少校
Now then, Major Wright.

16
00:04:23,140 --> 00:04:26,730
- 我跟你说说我的主意吧  - 我能拒绝吗？
- Let me tell you what I got in mind.   - Suppose I said no?

17
00:04:27,110 --> 00:04:28,440
我没听错吧,少校？
Did I hear you right, major?

18
00:04:28,810 --> 00:04:30,400
少来吧,山姆
Come on, Sam.

19
00:04:30,580 --> 00:04:32,910
我带两打人去执行过两次任务
I've taken two dozen men on two missions.

20
00:04:33,080 --> 00:04:35,210
活着回来的没几个
Except for a couple of them, they're all dead.

21
00:04:35,380 --> 00:04:38,180
是的,要不他们现在也早被绞死了
Yes, and most of them would have been hung by now anyway.

22
00:04:38,350 --> 00:04:40,720
有些人现在应该活着的
A few of them would still be alive.

23
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:43,920
先生,你要敢违抗拒军令,就得上军事法庭
Mister, you refuse an order, you face court-martial.

24
00:04:44,090 --> 00:04:47,930
如果军事法庭判你有罪,你就得在监狱等着战争结束吧
Court-martial finds you guilty and you'll finish the war in a military prison.

25
00:04:49,130 --> 00:04:51,060
欧洲战场上的大半军官...
Half the officers in the European theater...

26
00:04:51,230 --> 00:04:52,700
...都觉得你早该进监狱了
...think you belong there anyway.

27
00:04:52,870 --> 00:04:55,130
是,也许他们是对的
Well, maybe they're right.

28
00:04:58,040 --> 00:04:59,940
这张素描不错,将军！你画的？
That's a nice sketch, general. Your work?

29
00:05:00,110 --> 00:05:03,130
- 是的  - 真漂亮,将军！
- Well, yes.   - That's a beautiful sketch, general.

30
00:05:03,310 --> 00:05:06,910
这是上周我在一份德国秘密文件上看到的
It's my rendering of a secret German document I saw last week.

31
00:05:07,080 --> 00:05:09,640
- 你知道画的是什么吗？ - V2火箭吗？
- Do you know what it is?   - V2 rocket?

32
00:05:09,820 --> 00:05:12,310
比V2火箭还要厉害的东西
A much more powerful version than that.

33
00:05:12,490 --> 00:05:14,850
当德国人让这玩意上天的时候...
When the Germans make that baby operational...

34
00:05:15,020 --> 00:05:17,920
...纽约、华盛顿、莫斯科都在它的射程内
...it can reach New York, Washington, Moscow.

35
00:05:18,090 --> 00:05:19,620
这是A4导弹！
It's an A4 missile.

36
00:05:19,790 --> 00:05:22,890
德国人30年代中期就开始研究这种武器
The Germans were working on something like this in the mid-'30s.

37
00:05:23,060 --> 00:05:25,930
如果他们在这次大战中及时研制成功的话,...
If they made it operational in time for this war...

38
00:05:26,100 --> 00:05:28,630
...他们也许已经赢得了这场战争的胜利
...they probably would have won it already.

39
00:05:29,640 --> 00:05:33,330
哦,我会把素描给盟军参谋们看
Well, I'll pass that along to the Allied General Staff.

40
00:05:34,980 --> 00:05:39,310
假如有枚满载毒气的导弹在华盛顿引爆...
Supposing I'd painted a picture of a missile landing in Washington...

41
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:43,940
...结果会是一幅怎样的画面？
...and what the results would be if it were crammed full of poison gas?

42
00:05:44,120 --> 00:05:47,320
- 德国人不会使用毒气的,先生  - 希特勒已经狗急跳墙
- The Germans will never use gas, sir.   - Hitler's desperate.

43
00:05:48,520 --> 00:05:51,320
他会找到速战速决的方法
He's gotta find a means of achieving a quick victory.

44
00:05:51,490 --> 00:05:53,890
牵制美军和英军...
One that'll knock the Americans and the British out...

45
00:05:54,060 --> 00:05:56,260
...然后乘机将苏军击退
...and give him a chance to wipe out the Russians.

46
00:05:56,430 --> 00:05:58,830
我不跟你解释盟军的宏伟策略了...
I'm not gonna explain Allied grand strategy to you...

47
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:02,330
除非在法国一个修道院里...
...except that there are three dozen canisters...

48
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:06,340
...有36罐正处于试验阶段的致命神经毒气
...of an experimental but deadly nerve gas in a monastery in France.

49
00:06:06,510 --> 00:06:07,740
我们得在德军将其放入导弹前...
We want them taken out...

50
00:06:07,910 --> 00:06:10,640
...把它们给引爆
...before they can be launched by those new rockets.

51
00:06:10,810 --> 00:06:12,110
现在就得采取行动.
Now.

52
00:06:12,280 --> 00:06:14,180
- 出动空军吧  - 不行
- Use the Air Force.   - No, we can't.

53
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:18,440
他们在占领区抓了六名科学家...
There are six scientists, top experts in chemical warfare...

54
00:06:18,620 --> 00:06:20,640
...都是化学武器的顶级专家
...brought in from the occupied countries.

55
00:06:20,820 --> 00:06:22,720
我们得想办法把他们救出来
We want them rescued from that monastery.

56
00:06:23,060 --> 00:06:24,550
你去把他们从法国救出来！
You'll bring them out of France.

57
00:06:24,730 --> 00:06:26,720
不,你找错人了,将军
No, you got the wrong man, general.

58
00:06:26,890 --> 00:06:29,490
你知道的,我从没有执行过救援任务
You know, I'm not on any rescue mission.

59
00:06:29,660 --> 00:06:32,190
你去找找国际红十字会的电话吧
Get the phone number of the International Red Cross.

60
00:06:32,370 --> 00:06:36,770
现在,先生,你再去一次福布斯路的军人监狱
Right now, mister, you're on your way to Forbes Road military prison again.

61
00:06:36,940 --> 00:06:41,530
我的意见是：你再招募另一打脏鬼
My idea is that you start finding another Dirty Dozen.

62
00:06:41,780 --> 00:06:45,270
当然,这也许不是你的想法
Of course, that may not be your idea at all.

63
00:06:45,450 --> 00:06:48,240
- 那么,我觉得..  - 就这么定了,少校
- Well, I was thinking...   - Nothing further at this time, major.

64
00:06:48,420 --> 00:06:50,010
遵命,长官
Yes, sir.

65
00:07:14,710 --> 00:07:16,680
此人叫约瑟夫.史坦,少校
Got Joseph Stern here, major.

66
00:07:16,840 --> 00:07:18,740
判处绞刑
Death by hanging.

67
00:07:25,150 --> 00:07:27,020
你的履历很有趣,史坦
Interesting record, Stern.

68
00:07:27,190 --> 00:07:30,560
简洁明了,不过很有趣
I mean, brief, but interesting.

69
00:07:30,730 --> 00:07:33,160
就你那点事情,少校,我足以胜任
For what you want done, major, I qualify.

70
00:07:33,330 --> 00:07:35,660
哦,那是理所当然
Oh, there's no doubt about that.

71
00:07:35,830 --> 00:07:39,770
来看看,出生在德国,1935年来到美国
Let's see, born in Germany, came to the United States in 1935.

72
00:07:39,930 --> 00:07:43,060
1937年回到欧洲,西班牙
In '37 went back to Europe. Spain.

73
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:46,600
17岁时你就跟王党们并肩战斗了？
Fought on the Loyalist side when you were only 17 years old?

74
00:07:46,770 --> 00:07:48,610
我当时谎报了年龄
I lied about my age.

75
00:07:48,780 --> 00:07:52,370
在美国三次持枪抢劫,但没定罪
Three armed robberies back in the United States. No convictions.

76
00:07:52,550 --> 00:07:54,570
触犯联邦法律,持枪逃窜
A federal rap, gun running.

77
00:07:54,750 --> 00:07:56,480
这点你得承认吧
And you beat that one too.

78
00:07:56,650 --> 00:07:58,080
是,我逃跑时很走运
Yeah, I've been running in luck.

79
00:07:58,250 --> 00:08:01,450
是啊,你得好运到头了,最终被捕归案
Yeah, well, your luck ran out. They finally nailed you.

80
00:08:01,890 --> 00:08:04,760
你在酒吧喝酒时还杀了两个英国人
Drunk in a bar and killed an Englishman.

81
00:08:05,230 --> 00:08:07,190
你想因此被绞死？
You want to hang for that?

82
00:08:07,430 --> 00:08:08,760
- 不想  - 那好吧
- No.   - All right.

83
00:08:08,930 --> 00:08:11,060
让我们瞧瞧,你会说德语,会使用武器
Let's see, you speak German, you handle a weapon.

84
00:08:11,230 --> 00:08:13,630
问题是,我们是团队行动
You know, my problem is I gotta put a team together.

85
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:17,400
根据你的履历,你向来是独来独往
And according to this, you never played on any team except your own.

86
00:08:17,570 --> 00:08:21,470
听着,少校,你谈论的可不是打棒球
Look, major, this isn't a baseball game you're talking about.

87
00:08:21,640 --> 00:08:23,080
你谈的可是场战争
You're talking about war.

88
00:08:23,240 --> 00:08:25,970
你想去柏林再平安回来
You want to go all the way to Berlin and back.

89
00:08:26,210 --> 00:08:29,210
如果这是逃避绞刑的唯一办法...
If it's the only way I can beat the noose...

90
00:08:29,380 --> 00:08:31,610
...我就跟你去
...I'll follow you.

91
00:08:33,250 --> 00:08:35,150
顺便说一下...
Just for the record...

92
00:08:35,590 --> 00:08:37,850
...我当时在酒吧没有喝醉
...I wasn't drunk in that bar.

93
00:09:00,720 --> 00:09:02,810
- 打开吧  - 好了,瑞典小子
- All right, open up.   - Okay, Swede.

94
00:09:02,980 --> 00:09:04,950
把桶提出来
Bring out the bucket.

95
00:09:17,870 --> 00:09:20,630
埃里克.沃伦,绞刑犯
Eric Wallen, death by hanging.

96
00:09:20,800 --> 00:09:22,460
现在就准备绞死我吗？
They going to hang me now?

97
00:09:22,640 --> 00:09:23,900
不,还没到时候
No, no, no, not now.

98
00:09:24,070 --> 00:09:27,040
也许等会,但现在不用
Maybe later, but not now.

99
00:09:27,210 --> 00:09:30,040
- 你被关禁闭多久？ - 我记不清了
- How long you been in solitary?   - I'm not sure.

100
00:09:30,210 --> 00:09:32,370
他已经被关了25天,少校
He's been in solitary 25 days, major.

101
00:09:33,920 --> 00:09:36,180
哦,那他们为何要关你禁闭,瑞典小子？
And what did they send you to solitary for, Swede?

102
00:09:36,350 --> 00:09:38,550
他们想杀了我
They tried to kill me.

103
00:09:38,990 --> 00:09:42,350
他拒绝接受常规白喉疫苗接种,少校
He refused a routine diphtheria inoculation, major.

104
00:09:42,520 --> 00:09:43,620
医生要求他接种...
The doctor ordered it...

105
00:09:43,790 --> 00:09:46,560
...结果他把医生和另三个狱警都打伤送医院了
...and he put the doctor and three MPs in the hospital.

106
00:09:46,730 --> 00:09:48,350
干得不赖嘛
That's an impressive performance.

107
00:09:48,530 --> 00:09:53,090
来看看,你因为杀了两个英国人而来此地
Let's see, you killed two British citizens to get here in the first place.

108
00:09:53,470 --> 00:09:54,900
他们也想杀你吗？
They try to kill you too?

109
00:09:55,740 --> 00:09:58,000
他们想抢我的钱
They tried to take my money.

110
00:09:58,170 --> 00:10:01,570
哦,这是他们最糟糕的想法
Oh, that's the last bad idea they ever had.

111
00:10:01,880 --> 00:10:04,610
根据法医的报告...
According to the medical examiner's report...

112
00:10:04,780 --> 00:10:07,870
...你赤手空拳就把他们的头给打碎了？
...you crushed their heads with your bare hands?

113
00:10:08,850 --> 00:10:10,440
我现在觉得很抱歉
I'm sorry about that now.

114
00:10:10,620 --> 00:10:13,180
你不想从这禁闭室出去吗,瑞典小子？
How'd you like to get out of solitary, Swede?

115
00:10:13,350 --> 00:10:15,620
- 我要被绞死了,长官  - 有可能
- They're going to hang me, sir.   - Probably.

116
00:10:15,790 --> 00:10:17,490
但也可能不用
But maybe not.

117
00:10:17,690 --> 00:10:19,960
想不想在死前掐死几个德国人？
Would you like one last crack at the Germans first?

118
00:10:20,390 --> 00:10:22,360
能告诉我你的姓名吗,长官？
Could you tell me your name, sir?

119
00:10:22,660 --> 00:10:25,190
莱特少校。记住了,大兵？
Major Wright. And you remember that, soldier!

120
00:10:25,370 --> 00:10:27,100
因为从现在起...
Because from here on in...

121
00:10:27,270 --> 00:10:30,970
...我就是你生命中至关重要的人
...I don't think there's anyone else who will be all that important to you.

122
00:10:45,520 --> 00:10:48,080
今晚我们开会有几个原因
I brought you together tonight for a number of reasons.

123
00:10:48,260 --> 00:10:50,380
其中之一是观看英国情报部门...
One of them is to view some secret footage...

124
00:10:50,560 --> 00:10:52,750
...在德国的内线获得的...
...made available to British Intelligence...

125
00:10:52,930 --> 00:10:55,790
...秘密胶片
...by sources inside Germany.

126
00:10:56,100 --> 00:10:58,030
请关灯
Lights, please.

127
00:11:00,970 --> 00:11:03,900
这部影片是在纳粹实验部门管理的...
The locale of this film is a small hospital...

128
00:11:04,070 --> 00:11:07,800
...一个小医院里拍摄的
...maintained by SS experimental units near Schierling.

129
00:11:07,980 --> 00:11:11,840
据悉,不到两个月前希特勒...
Our information is that this film was shown to Adolf Hitler...

130
00:11:12,010 --> 00:11:15,110
...和他的部长阿尔伯特.施佩尔...
...and his production genius, Reichsminister Albert Speer...

131
00:11:15,280 --> 00:11:16,680
...观看了此片
...less than two months ago.

132
00:11:21,020 --> 00:11:25,020
她吸入了少量的神经性毒气...
She is being given a small dosage of a new nerve gas...

133
00:11:25,190 --> 00:11:29,320
...此毒气是法国纳粹占领区的科学家研制的
...developed by scientists working in France under SS control.

134
00:11:41,280 --> 00:11:43,510
现在毒气量在加大
More gas is pumped into the room.

135
00:11:47,350 --> 00:11:50,410
她的肺部因吸入毒气而衰竭
By now, her lungs are collapsed by the gas.

136
00:11:52,450 --> 00:11:53,890
心跳开始减弱
Her heart has slowed.

137
00:11:54,520 --> 00:11:57,290
脑部陷于瘫痪
Her brain is paralyzed.

138
00:11:57,530 --> 00:12:00,020
她死了
And she's dead.

139
00:12:06,970 --> 00:12:08,990
请开灯
Lights, please.

140
00:12:12,640 --> 00:12:15,230
山姆,你觉得在德军开始使用此武器前...
Sam, how much time do you think we have...

141
00:12:15,410 --> 00:12:17,900
...我们还有多少时间？
...before the Germans start using this stuff?

142
00:12:18,250 --> 00:12:19,870
没多少时间了
Not much.

143
00:12:20,050 --> 00:12:22,520
英国情报部门已经确认...
British Intelligence is convinced...

144
00:12:22,680 --> 00:12:25,480
...德军马上将用V2火箭把此种毒气...
...that canisters of this gas can shortly be delivered...

145
00:12:25,650 --> 00:12:29,650
...发射到英国的群岛上去...
...to every part of the British Isles by V2 rocket...

146
00:12:30,120 --> 00:12:34,360
...这样德军就不会牺牲一兵一卒了
...without the loss of a single German life.

147
00:12:34,530 --> 00:12:36,790
先生们,你们想想
Think about it, gentlemen.

148
00:12:43,840 --> 00:12:45,400
你全是为了我好吗,将军？
All that for my benefit, general?

149
00:12:45,570 --> 00:12:47,670
你不是开玩笑吧
You have to be kidding.

150
00:12:48,710 --> 00:12:49,970
有效果吗？
Did it work?

151
00:12:50,140 --> 00:12:51,410
差不多
More or less.

152
00:12:51,580 --> 00:12:53,480
你知道,我不是美军的忠实拥护者...
You know, I'm not that fond of the Army...

153
00:12:53,650 --> 00:12:56,240
...但是看过纳粹的实验片后...
...but after watching those Nazi training films...

154
00:12:56,420 --> 00:12:59,350
...我对那帮畜生越发恨之入骨
...I realize I hate those bastards even more.

155
00:13:00,190 --> 00:13:03,350
圣米歇尔的圣佛朗西斯修道院
The Abbey of St. Francis of St. Michel.

156
00:13:03,520 --> 00:13:05,150
毒气就在那里
That's where it's at.

157
00:13:05,330 --> 00:13:08,160
这是圣器室,这是纳粹总部
The sacristy, SS quarters.

158
00:13:08,330 --> 00:13:11,130
科学家就被关在老修道院的宿舍里...
The scientists are being held in the old monk's quarters...

159
00:13:11,300 --> 00:13:13,460
...毒气弹就在地窖里
...and the canisters are in the wine cellar.

160
00:13:15,570 --> 00:13:17,430
这是你的任务,少校
Your orders, major.

161
00:13:18,310 --> 00:13:20,400
你将带12个被判死刑...
You will take 12 general prisoners...

162
00:13:20,570 --> 00:13:23,630
...或长期徒刑的犯人去执行任务
...convicted and sentenced to death or to long terms of imprisonment.

163
00:13:23,810 --> 00:13:26,040
你要训练这些犯人使之具备相应的能力...
You will train and qualify the prisoners...

164
00:13:26,210 --> 00:13:28,340
...再将他们秘密送到法国
...and deliver them secretly behind the lines.

165
00:13:28,520 --> 00:13:31,250
你们要毁掉预定目标...
You will attack and destroy your assigned target...

166
00:13:31,420 --> 00:13:33,940
...拯救六个被押科学家
...and you will free the six captive scientists.

167
00:13:34,160 --> 00:13:37,450
如果这些囚犯触任何军规...
Any breach of security, any failure of discipline...

168
00:13:37,630 --> 00:13:40,320
...都将被送回监狱...
...and the prisoners go right back where they came from...

169
00:13:40,490 --> 00:13:43,430
...并且立即执行判决
...for summary execution of sentence.

170
00:13:44,970 --> 00:13:48,590
埃内斯托.费里奇,20年苦役
Ferruci, Ernesto. Twenty years hard labor.

171
00:13:49,940 --> 00:13:52,740
得给他好好上一课
Might add a little class to the act.

172
00:13:54,240 --> 00:13:57,110
好了,起立
Okay, Pops, on your feet.

173
00:13:57,680 --> 00:14:00,370
放松点,费里奇,抱歉打扰你服刑了
All right, at ease, Ferruci. Sorry to disturb your labors.

174
00:14:00,550 --> 00:14:03,110
没关系,少校,我还有20年刑期
No problem, major. I got 20 years to finish it.

175
00:14:03,280 --> 00:14:04,770
是嘛...
Well, if you...

176
00:14:04,950 --> 00:14:06,680
- 你多大了？ - 44岁
- How old are you?   - Forty-four.

177
00:14:06,850 --> 00:14:08,850
- 再说一次？ - 48岁
- Come again?   - Forty-eight?

178
00:14:09,660 --> 00:14:11,490
堪萨斯警察局说...
Well, the Kansas City police department...

179
00:14:11,660 --> 00:14:13,560
...你已经52了
...got you listed here for 52.

180
00:14:14,200 --> 00:14:16,720
哦,我觉得年龄大一点参军的话...
Oh, I thought the Army might be good for my...

181
00:14:16,900 --> 00:14:18,260
...会比较安全
...my security in my old age.

182
00:14:18,430 --> 00:14:20,260
于是我向征兵的长官撒了谎
So I lied to the recruiting officer.

183
00:14:20,430 --> 00:14:22,900
那是什么？是我写的诗
Yeah, what's that? I write poetry.

184
00:14:23,070 --> 00:14:25,060
你写诗？是的
Do you? Yes.

185
00:14:27,270 --> 00:14:29,470
那蓝色小小的...
At that little tent of blue

186
00:14:30,210 --> 00:14:32,510
囚犯们称之为天空的地方
Which prisoners call the sky

187
00:14:32,780 --> 00:14:34,650
这首狱中诗写得不错
That's a good piece of jailhouse poetry.

188
00:14:34,820 --> 00:14:37,340
- 谢谢你,少校！ - 谢谢你,少校？
- Thank you, major.   - Thank you, major.

189
00:14:37,520 --> 00:14:41,320
确实是首不错的狱中诗,是50年前...
It was a great piece of jailhouse poetry when Oscar Wilde wrote it...

190
00:14:41,490 --> 00:14:43,620
...奥斯卡.王尔德在雷丁监狱写的
...fifty years ago in Reading Jail.

191
00:14:43,790 --> 00:14:45,020
奥斯卡.王尔德？
Oscar Wilde?

192
00:14:45,190 --> 00:14:47,790
难怪听起来耳熟呢
I thought it sounded kind of familiar.

193
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:50,290
你就靠作假来生活吧？
You really had it made, didn't you, Ernesto?

194
00:14:50,460 --> 00:14:53,490
做假石油配给券、假食物配给券、假英镑...
With your phony gas coupons, food stamps...

195
00:14:53,670 --> 00:14:56,640
...你一个人都可以搞一个黑市了
...counterfeit British pounds. You're a one-man black market.

196
00:14:56,800 --> 00:14:59,170
有时候人会不顾一切的,少校
Sometimes a man gets desperate, major.

197
00:14:59,340 --> 00:15:01,100
我遇到了一个英国女孩
I met this English girl.

198
00:15:01,280 --> 00:15:04,470
她比我年轻25岁
She was 25 years younger than myself.

199
00:15:04,950 --> 00:15:08,110
- 我昏头了  - 还好她不是双胞胎
- I lost my head.   - It's a good thing she wasn't twins.

200
00:15:08,280 --> 00:15:09,650
否则我们早就战败了
We would've lost the war.

201
00:15:10,420 --> 00:15:12,010
我不明白,费里奇
I don't know, Ferruci.

202
00:15:12,190 --> 00:15:14,810
你是个反叛人物,小偷
You're a con man and a thief.

203
00:15:14,990 --> 00:15:17,580
但这个任务可比坐20年牢危险多了
But where I'm going, they don't just give you 20 years.

204
00:15:17,760 --> 00:15:20,920
你会死得很难看的
They turn you upside down and let your guts roll out.

205
00:15:21,360 --> 00:15:24,090
我觉得你年龄大了,不适合这个任务
No. I think you're a little too old for this project.

206
00:15:24,270 --> 00:15:26,500
我不老,我身材保持得不错
I'm not too old, major. I'm in good shape.

207
00:15:26,670 --> 00:15:29,100
也许我可以教导你手下的新人
Maybe I can help you with some of the young kids.

208
00:15:29,270 --> 00:15:31,070
老实说吧,少校
Honest to God, major.

209
00:15:31,240 --> 00:15:34,000
我可不想死在铁窗里
I don't want to die behind these walls.

210
00:15:34,780 --> 00:15:36,240
好吧,那你听着
Okay, now, you listen.

211
00:15:36,410 --> 00:15:39,610
你若在法国再违反军规就死定了,明白吗？
You foul up one time and you die in France. You understand?

212
00:15:40,610 --> 00:15:42,310
我不知道具体需要什么
Now, I don't know what I'm gonna need.

213
00:15:42,480 --> 00:15:45,510
法国配给券、食物券...
French ration books, food stamps...

214
00:15:45,690 --> 00:15:49,920
...德国身份证、工作签证、现金
...German identification cards, occupation passports, currency.

215
00:15:50,090 --> 00:15:53,220
我要的东西都很急,而且要做得很好
But whatever I need, I need fast. And I need it perfect.

216
00:15:53,390 --> 00:15:54,550
我明白了,长官
You got it, sir.

217
00:15:56,330 --> 00:15:58,460
你可千万别想骗过我这个行骗老手
Never con a con man, Pops.

218
00:16:00,100 --> 00:16:03,160
这是罗兰德.韦博和大卫.韦博
This is Webber, Ronald and David.

219
00:16:03,340 --> 00:16:06,070
都被判30年徒刑
Thirty years imprisonment. Each.

220
00:16:07,170 --> 00:16:09,970
我觉得该跟你俩一起谈谈了
Well, I thought I'd talk to you two boys together.

221
00:16:10,140 --> 00:16:13,550
- 既然你们是同伙  - 我总是很照顾大卫
- Since you're partners in everything.   - I always try to look after Davie.

222
00:16:13,710 --> 00:16:16,910
哦,那你就是老大,你可把小兄弟给害惨了
Oh, you're the one. Well, look what happened to little brother Davie.

223
00:16:17,080 --> 00:16:20,580
你害他坐30年牢,还说在照顾他
You got him 30 years and you're still taking care of Davie.

224
00:16:20,750 --> 00:16:24,210
- 罗兰德劝过我金盆洗手  - 显然他的说服力不够
- Ronnie's tried to talk me out of things.   - Obviously not enough, right?

225
00:16:24,390 --> 00:16:27,620
你们本来是赛车手,看看你们沦落成什么了？
You start off as race car drivers, and you wind up as what?

226
00:16:27,800 --> 00:16:29,560
窃车贼和杀人犯
Auto thieves and killers.

227
00:16:29,730 --> 00:16:31,220
我问你们
Let me ask you something.

228
00:16:32,430 --> 00:16:35,300
做这些勾当能赢得金杯吗？
Do they give gold cups for that kind of dumb?

229
00:16:35,800 --> 00:16:39,300
好了,放松点。你们最好的成绩是哪年取得的？
All right, relax. What's the last good year, boys?

230
00:16:40,340 --> 00:16:42,400
39年,少校
'39, major.

231
00:16:42,610 --> 00:16:46,910
我们离开农场,驾着玛莎拉蒂3.2型去参加印地车赛
We left the farm, went up to the Indy with a 3.2 Maserati.

232
00:16:47,080 --> 00:16:48,480
当时我们差不多快赢了
Man, we almost took it all.

233
00:16:49,250 --> 00:16:51,150
后来怎么回事？没油了？
And then what happened? You run out of gas?

234
00:16:51,590 --> 00:16:52,810
不是
Not exactly.

235
00:16:52,990 --> 00:16:55,050
第二年我们的农场破产了,少校
We lost the farm the next year, major.

236
00:16:55,220 --> 00:16:57,850
坏事连连,我们一无所有
One thing after another, everything went down the drain.

237
00:16:58,030 --> 00:16:59,820
我问你们
Let me ask you something.

238
00:17:00,760 --> 00:17:02,460
你们两个都会说德语吗？
You boys, you sprechen Sie Deutsch?

239
00:17:02,660 --> 00:17:04,150
你是说德语？
You mean German?

240
00:17:04,370 --> 00:17:07,460
多年前我父亲离家出走后,我就几乎没听人说过了
I hardly heard it since Daddy pulled up stakes and took off years ago.

241
00:17:07,640 --> 00:17:09,400
好吧,你们长得像德国人
All right, you look German.

242
00:17:09,570 --> 00:17:11,000
穿上军装...
Put a uniform on you...

243
00:17:11,170 --> 00:17:13,660
...闭上嘴,会有怎样的效果？
...keep your mouths shut and then what happens?

244
00:17:13,840 --> 00:17:16,900
人们肯定会以为你们来自非洲军团
People gonna think you stepped out of the Afrika Korps.

245
00:17:17,340 --> 00:17:19,010
因此你才选上我们,少校？
Is that why you're picking us, major?

246
00:17:19,180 --> 00:17:21,150
我选上你们是因为你们是赛车手
I'm picking you because you're drivers.

247
00:17:21,320 --> 00:17:23,880
偷懒的话我可不放过你们
One slowdown and I'll run right over you.

248
00:17:26,520 --> 00:17:28,510
- 是,长官  - 是,长官
- Yes, sir.   - Yes, sir.

249
00:17:30,020 --> 00:17:32,490
你现在进入的是重犯区,少校
You are now entering maximum security, major.

250
00:17:32,660 --> 00:17:34,590
我知道了...
I see. One....

251
00:17:34,960 --> 00:17:37,620
方提纳的狱室与其他重犯隔了三个房间？
You keep three empty cells between Fontenac and the others?

252
00:17:37,800 --> 00:17:40,060
是的,少校,这是为了防止行刑前...
Right, major. The idea is to prevent the others...

253
00:17:40,230 --> 00:17:42,700
...有人接近他
...from getting to him before we hang him.

254
00:17:42,870 --> 00:17:45,130
我这次挑的人可真不错呐,嗯哼？
Well, I really picked some beauties this time, huh?

255
00:17:45,310 --> 00:17:47,170
少校心里应该有数
I'm sure the major nows what he's doing.

256
00:17:47,340 --> 00:17:49,280
但愿如此,中士
I hope you're right, sergeant.

257
00:17:54,820 --> 00:17:56,250
西蒙斯！
Simmons!

258
00:18:18,270 --> 00:18:20,400
你敢轻举妄动我就打爆你的头
You move an eyelash and I'll blow your head off.

259
00:18:32,420 --> 00:18:34,320
你可以把他从名单上划掉了,少校
You can scratch him off the list, major.

260
00:18:34,490 --> 00:18:36,510
我们会以越狱罪把他除名
And we'll hang him for escape.

261
00:18:40,960 --> 00:18:42,160
别碰他一根汗毛
Don't touch him.

262
00:18:43,460 --> 00:18:44,800
他是个绝佳的人选
He's perfect.

263
00:18:52,870 --> 00:18:54,100
对！
Yeah!

264
00:18:55,680 --> 00:18:57,200
刺！
Lunge!

265
00:18:59,280 --> 00:19:01,140
刺！
Lunge!

266
00:19:02,380 --> 00:19:04,480
左闪！
Left parry!

267
00:19:05,350 --> 00:19:08,650
右闪！左闪！
Right parry! Left parry!

268
00:19:08,990 --> 00:19:11,250
你就这点能耐吗,马丁内兹？
Best you got, Martinez?

269
00:19:11,930 --> 00:19:14,190
- 刺！ - 来啊
- Lunge!   - Come on.

270
00:19:14,360 --> 00:19:15,830
- 左闪！ - 来啊
- Left parry!   - Come on.

271
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:18,120
- 快来  - 右闪！
- Let's do it.   - Right parry!

272
00:19:18,300 --> 00:19:20,230
- 刺中你了  - 刺！
- I got you.   - Lunge.

273
00:19:21,300 --> 00:19:22,790
右闪
Right parry.

274
00:19:22,970 --> 00:19:24,940
- 来吧  - 大声点
- Come on.   - I can't hear you.

275
00:19:25,570 --> 00:19:26,560
快刺
Now lunge.

276
00:19:27,740 --> 00:19:30,070
好了,归队,归队
All right, recover. Recover.

277
00:19:30,240 --> 00:19:31,970
我很惊讶
I'm surprised.

278
00:19:32,910 --> 00:19:36,010
你们大多数都是死囚吧？
I mean, most of you are in here for capital offenses, right?

279
00:19:36,180 --> 00:19:38,710
但你们看上去就像群没杀过人的傻子
It looks like the only thing you've ever killed is time.

280
00:19:38,890 --> 00:19:41,860
上刺刀。德军出现时你们怎么办？
Put that on. So, what are you gonna do when the Krauts show up?

281
00:19:42,360 --> 00:19:44,790
把法庭判决书念给他们听？
Read them your trial transcripts?

282
00:19:44,960 --> 00:19:46,790
你,瑞典小子
You, Swede.

283
00:19:47,830 --> 00:19:49,690
接着
Catch.

284
00:19:50,660 --> 00:19:52,790
拿住,它又不会咬你
Hold onto it, it won't bite.

285
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:54,560
我是你的敌人
I'm the enemy.

286
00:19:54,940 --> 00:19:56,700
你跟我单挑
It's you and me.

287
00:19:57,870 --> 00:19:59,270
来吧,刺我
Go ahead, lunge.

288
00:19:59,440 --> 00:20:00,770
少校,我会杀了你的
Major, I'll kill you.

289
00:20:04,110 --> 00:20:06,380
史上有两次大的战争
There have been two great wars.

290
00:20:06,550 --> 00:20:08,340
瑞典两次都幸免于战
Sweden has managed to stay out of both.

291
00:20:08,520 --> 00:20:11,810
逃过了一战和二战的硝烟,原因是什么
World War I and World War ll. I wonder why.

292
00:20:12,190 --> 00:20:14,680
因为你们是热爱和平、聪明过人的民族？
Is it because you're a peace-loving, intelligent people?

293
00:20:14,860 --> 00:20:17,480
- 还是因为你们是懦夫？ - 少校,别这样
- Or is it because you're cowards?   - Major, don't.

294
00:20:17,660 --> 00:20:20,130
- 别激怒我  - 我是在激怒你,瑞典小子...
- Don't push me.   - I'm pushing you, Swede...

295
00:20:20,290 --> 00:20:23,320
...因为我想知道你究竟是什么种？
...because I want to find out where you're coming from, all right?

296
00:20:23,500 --> 00:20:25,560
你到底是战士...
Now, are you a soldier...

297
00:20:25,730 --> 00:20:28,060
- ...还是孬种？ - 瑞典小子,杀了他
- ... or are you a coward?   - Kill him, Swede.

298
00:20:28,240 --> 00:20:30,070
- 上啊,瑞典小子  - 刺死他
- Come on, Swede.   - Stick him, Swede.

299
00:20:30,240 --> 00:20:32,570
- 把他干掉  - 杀了他
- Put him away, Swede.   - Get him, Swede.

300
00:20:32,740 --> 00:20:34,000
少校,别说了！
Major, cut it out!

301
00:20:34,170 --> 00:20:35,870
我们都想知道
They want to know.

302
00:20:36,040 --> 00:20:39,170
你是男子汉还是懦夫？刺吧
Are you a man or a gutless punk? Lunge.

303
00:20:45,090 --> 00:20:46,990
要是德军把刀插到你的后脑上...
What happens when the Kraut comes along...

304
00:20:47,150 --> 00:20:50,420
...你会怎样？
...and shoves this steel through to the back of your head?

305
00:20:56,500 --> 00:20:58,660
这部分训练到此为止
That's enough for this session.

306
00:21:13,410 --> 00:21:16,580
好了,到了,列队
Okay, okay, let's go. Line up.

307
00:21:16,950 --> 00:21:18,650
- 快点  - 好了
- Move it.   - All right.

308
00:21:18,820 --> 00:21:21,150
大家都下车
Everybody out of the trucks.

309
00:21:22,420 --> 00:21:24,520
快点下来！
Fall in. Move it!

310
00:21:26,630 --> 00:21:28,600
列好队后...
And when you're ready...

311
00:21:29,030 --> 00:21:30,290
...报数
...count off.

312
00:21:30,460 --> 00:21:32,360
- 1  - 2
- One.   - Two.

313
00:21:32,530 --> 00:21:34,120
- 3  - 4
- Three.  - Four.

314
00:21:34,300 --> 00:21:35,600
- 5  - 6
- Five.   - Six.

315
00:21:35,770 --> 00:21:36,790
- 7  - 8
- Seven.   - Eight.

316
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:38,030
- 9  - 10
- Nine.   - Ten.

317
00:21:38,210 --> 00:21:39,300
- 11  - 12
- Eleven.   - Twelve.

318
00:21:39,470 --> 00:21:41,500
- 13  - 你们只有12个人...
- Thirteen.   - There'll be only 12 of you...

319
00:21:41,680 --> 00:21:42,800
...能去执行任务
...going on the mission.

320
00:21:42,980 --> 00:21:44,600
所以你们得记住
So be on your toes.

321
00:21:44,780 --> 00:21:47,110
有一个人要回到监狱去
One will go back to prison.

322
00:21:47,650 --> 00:21:51,240
实战训练课程...
The infiltration under the live ammunition course...

323
00:21:51,420 --> 00:21:54,410
...通常保留到训练的最后一周
...is usually reserved for the last week of training.

324
00:21:54,590 --> 00:21:56,520
但我们这个训练...
But the first week and the last week...

325
00:21:56,690 --> 00:21:58,320
...只有一周时间
...are one and the same around here.

326
00:21:58,490 --> 00:22:02,990
此外,我希望用真枪实弹快速决定人选
And besides, I want a fast rundown on you people under fire.

327
00:22:03,160 --> 00:22:07,120
场地那端有挺.30口径的机关枪...
The 30-caliber machine gun at the other end of the field...

328
00:22:07,300 --> 00:22:10,570
...将会从距地面36英寸高的地方扫射
...is locked in to fire at 36 inches above the ground.

329
00:22:10,740 --> 00:22:12,070
相当于3英尺
That's three feet.

330
00:22:12,240 --> 00:22:13,900
仔细听着
Listen carefully.

331
00:22:14,070 --> 00:22:16,240
把你们的头埋低
Keep your heads down.

332
00:22:16,810 --> 00:22:19,180
把屁股紧贴在地面
And you keep your butts close to the ground.

333
00:22:19,350 --> 00:22:21,840
这样就很容易通过了
Then you should get through it easily.

334
00:22:22,650 --> 00:22:24,950
如果你们惊慌失措...
But if you panic...

335
00:22:25,520 --> 00:22:27,490
...就别想参加这个任务了
...then this mission is all over for you.

336
00:22:27,650 --> 00:22:29,450
好了,趴下
All right, hit the ground.

337
00:22:31,830 --> 00:22:33,850
一次两人！
Two at a time!

